                            <comment id="19503" author="springboy" created="Sun, 10 Sep 2006 02:58:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Matt&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I hear you, but well, the answer to this is... don&apos;t do that &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The various form tags need to be used inside the scope of a surrounding &amp;lt;form/&amp;gt; tag, and I have emphasized one line of text in the reference documentation to that effect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers&lt;br/&gt;
Rick&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="19875" author="rwells" created="Mon, 25 Sep 2006 05:52:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Couldn&apos;t this be solved with the same technique that OptionTag uses to verify that it is under SelectTag?  That would allow for a clear and concise error message.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
